snippet: Security forces early Wednesday stormed the central plaza in Kiev where protesters have been rallying against the government of President Viktor F. Yanukovich.
abstract: Battalions of Ukrainian security forces storm central plaza in Kiev where protesters have been rallying against the government of President Viktor F Yanukovich for more than two weeks; capital is in virtual lockdown; United States condemns use of force against protesters.

byline.original: By DAVID M. HERSZENHORN and ANDREW E. KRAMER
byline.contributor: Michael R. Gordon contributed reporting from Washington, and Oksana Lyachynska from Kiev.

lead_paragraph: Security forces early Wednesday stormed the central plaza in Kiev where protesters have been rallying against the government of President Viktor F. Yanukovich.

headline.main: Police Push Into Kiev Square as Crisis Grows
headline.print_headline: Police Push Into Kiev Square as Crisis Grows
